 Challange the given problem by first solving for $n$ in the equation $2n + 5 = 16$.

Step 1: Solve for $n$.
\begin{align*}
2n + 5 &= 16 \\
2n &= 16 - 5 \\
2n &= 11 \\
n &= \frac{11}{2}
\end{align*}

Step 2: Substitute the value of $n$ into the expression $2n - 3$.
\begin{align*}
2n - 3 &= 2 \left(\frac{11}{2}\right) - 3 \\
&= 11 - 3 \\
&= 8
\end{align*}

Thus, the value of the expression $2n - 3$ is $\boxed{8}$.

